-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - July 17
-- 
-- Thu Jul 17, 2014 02:40AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, July 17 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- A Bulgarian court lifted the banking secret over some banking accounts at the troubled Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB>, sources from the prosecutors' office said, adding that the request was linked to the investigation into deputy central bank governor Tsvetan Gounev accused of abuse of office. (24 Chasa, Capital, Monitor, Presa. Standart, Sega, Trud) -- The ruling Socialists have demanded more time to discuss the proposed increase of budget deficit to 2.7 percent of GDP and new debt of up to 3.4 billion levs for this year, while opposition GERB party demanded a budget increase of up to 7 percent. (24 Chasa, Presa, Standart, Trud) -- Torrential rains have flooded resorts at Bulgaria's southern Black Sea coast, blocking roads and camping sites. (24 Chasa, Duma, Presa, Monitor, Standart, Sega, Trud) -- Bulgarian government has asked Germany's Deutsche Bahn to provide an restructuring plan and set up an international management for the struggling state railways operator BDZ, Transport Minister Daniel Papazov said.(24 Chasa, Standart, Sega)